summary:
The Security Council,

Recalling resolutions 2216 (2015), 2722 (2024), and 2739 (2024) on Yemen and the Red Sea,
Condemns Houthi attacks on merchant and commercial vessels,
Reaffirms respect for Red Sea coastal States' sovereignty and territorial integrity,
Stresses maritime security's importance for global supply chains and economic development,

1. Extends reporting request in resolution 2722 (2024) until July 15, 2025;
2. Demands Houthis cease attacks on vessels, release M/V Galaxy Leader and its crew;
3. Emphasizes addressing root causes, including conflicts and regional tensions;
4. Notes advanced weaponry use, demands Member States stop arming Houthis;
5. Urges caution, restraint, and diplomatic efforts to prevent escalation;
6. Decides to remain seized of this matter.
